“These cartels are stupid if they think they can dig themselves out under the radar,” Laura Duffy, the U.S. District Attorney for Southern California, told a news conference outside a warehouse in San Diego, where one end of the tunnel had been discovered.
Speaking to the drug gangs, Duffy assured: “If you continue to build such tunnels and try to use them, we are determined to make that a huge waste of your dirty money.”
Both the US authorities and the Mexican security forces are in a constant battle against the drug cartels.
Since 2006, more than 77,000 people have been killed in Mexico in connection with drug-related crime.
Designed by experts
