Vegan diets require plant-based alternatives to eggs, milk, and dairy products.
Pureed tofu with plant cream, for example, is a quark substitute.
The World Vegetarian Day is celebrated on November 1st.
The Vegetarian Federation Germany proposes a number of vegan alternatives on the occasion of the World Vegan Day on 1 November:
Pure plant margarine is a good alternative to butter, yogurt is replaced by soy yogurt.
Instead of milk, soy, oat, almond or rice milk can be used.
Whipped plant cream replaces conventional whipped cream.
There are also plant-based alternatives to eggs.
A half crushed, ripe banana, for example, can replace an egg as a binder in a cake.
Also 50 grams of applesauce or a tablespoon of ground flaxseed plus three tablespoons of water are suitable for this.
Loose doughs become doughs instead of using egg, for example, with a mixture of a teaspoon of baking soda, a tablespoon of cornstarch, and three tablespoons of mineral water.
But even 50 grams of soy yogurt or silken tofu can fulfill this purpose.
According to Vebu, around 800,000 people in Germany currently eat vegan, i.e. purely plant-based.
